<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="198" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1199,1622]" pageId="6" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1524,1550]" pageId="6" pageNumber="198">Remarks.</emphasis>
On 
<date box="[362,570,1524,1550]" pageId="6" pageNumber="198" value="2019-02-06">6th February 2019</date>
, an incomplete remain of 
<taxonomicName box="[857,1068,1524,1550]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Platysodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madoni">
<emphasis box="[857,1068,1524,1550]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="198">Platysodes madoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found at Panxi of the Mount Fanjingshan, northeastern 
<collectingRegion box="[451,550,1560,1586]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="6" pageNumber="198">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[564,631,1560,1586]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="198">China</collectingCountry>
(Kai-Chen Ou-Yang, personal communication, 
<date box="[1176,1327,1560,1586]" pageId="6" pageNumber="198" value="2020-08">August 2020</date>
). This record extends the distributional range of this species northward (
<figureCitation box="[863,948,1596,1622]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1722,1746]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,273,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-61@7.[164,1423,273,1699]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 28. Known distribution of Platysodes Westwood, 1873 species (inset photograph shows the dead specimen of P. ma- doni Bourgoin, 1923 found at Mount Fanjingshan, Guizhou, China, provided by Ka-Chen Ou-Yang). Distribution data take from Qiu et al. (2015) and specimens examined in the present work." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4301825" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4301825/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="198">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
